theorem Topology.isClosed_and_isOpen_of_frontier_eq_empty
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    frontier A = (∅ : Set X) → IsClosed A ∧ IsOpen A := by
  intro hFrontier
  -- From `frontier A = ∅` we get `closure A ⊆ interior A`.
  have hSub : closure A ⊆ interior A := by
    intro x hxClos
    by_cases hxInt : x ∈ interior A
    · exact hxInt
    ·
      have : x ∈ closure A \ interior A := ⟨hxClos, hxInt⟩
      have : x ∈ (∅ : Set X) := by
        simpa [frontier, hFrontier] using this
      exact this.elim
  -- `interior A ⊆ A` and `A ⊆ closure A` are always true.
  have hIntSubA : interior A ⊆ A := interior_subset
  have hASubClos : A ⊆ closure A := subset_closure
  -- Hence all three sets coincide.
  have hClosEqInt : closure A = interior A := by
    apply Set.Subset.antisymm
    · exact hSub
    · exact Topology.interior_subset_closure (A := A)
  have hClosEqA : closure A = A := by
    apply Set.Subset.antisymm
    · exact
        (hClosEqInt.trans hIntSubA)   -- `closure A ⊆ interior A ⊆ A`
    · exact hASubClos
  have hIntEqA : interior A = A := by
    apply Set.Subset.antisymm
    · exact hIntSubA
    ·
      have : interior A ⊆ closure A :=
        Topology.interior_subset_closure (A := A)
      simpa [hClosEqA] using this
  -- Conclude that `A` is both closed and open.
  have hClosed : IsClosed A := by
    simpa [hClosEqA] using (isClosed_closure (s := A))
  have hOpen : IsOpen A := by
    simpa [hIntEqA] using (isOpen_interior : IsOpen (interior A))
  exact And.intro hClosed hOpen

theorem Topology.image_closure_subset_closure_image
    {X Y : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] [TopologicalSpace Y]
    {f : X → Y} (hf : Continuous f) {A : Set X} :
    f '' closure A ⊆ closure (f '' A) := by
  intro y hy
  rcases hy with ⟨x, hx_closure, rfl⟩
  -- We show that `f x` satisfies the closure property with respect to `f '' A`.
  refine (mem_closure_iff).2 ?_
  intro U hU_open hfxU
  -- The preimage of `U` under `f` is an open neighbourhood of `x`.
  have hPreimageOpen : IsOpen (f ⁻¹' U) := hU_open.preimage hf
  have hxPreimage : x ∈ f ⁻¹' U := hfxU
  -- Since `x ∈ closure A`, this neighbourhood intersects `A`.
  have hInter : ((f ⁻¹' U) ∩ A).Nonempty :=
    (mem_closure_iff.1 hx_closure) (f ⁻¹' U) hPreimageOpen hxPreimage
  -- Project the intersection point through `f` to obtain the desired intersection.
  rcases hInter with ⟨z, ⟨hzPre, hzA⟩⟩
  exact ⟨f z, ⟨z, hzA, rfl⟩, hzPre⟩

theorem Topology.isClosed_frontier {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    IsClosed (frontier A) := by
  simpa [frontier] using
    (Topology.isClosed_boundary (X := X) (A := A))

theorem Topology.closure_eq_self_union_frontier {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    {A : Set X} :
    closure A = A ∪ frontier A := by
  ext x
  constructor
  · intro hxClos
    by_cases hA : x ∈ A
    · exact Or.inl hA
    ·
      have hxNotInt : x ∉ interior A := by
        intro hxInt
        exact hA (interior_subset hxInt)
      have hxFront : x ∈ frontier A := And.intro hxClos hxNotInt
      exact Or.inr hxFront
  · intro hx
    cases hx with
    | inl hA      => exact subset_closure hA
    | inr hFront  => exact hFront.1
